<h2 class="portal_h">Beatrice Brown</h2>
<div id="portal_div">
  <%= image_tag ("brown.png"),class:"about_img" %>
  <p>
    <strong>Beatrice Brown </strong>
    is an artist whose multidisciplinary practice involves music, film, performance and painting. Musically she has collaborated with numerous artists
    including post punk band Selfish Cunt, Warrior Charge (Tricky), Jeffrey Lee Pierce project (Iggy Pop, Nick Cave, Deborah Harry), performance art group Joan
    of Ass as well as Steve Stella New (Rich Kids, PIL, Iggy Pop, Pearl Harbour) with whom she released two albums ‘Beastiality’ and ‘Stars and Wronguns' under
    the name of Beastellabeast. She performs regularly with Deadcuts. Her paintings, performance, sound and video works explore themes surrounding esoteric
    sexuality, ritual, out of body experience and possession and have been shown at ICA, the Roundhouse, 1 Exhibition Road, Pure Evil Gallery and Millenium St
    Ives, The Cornish Bienalle, Flowers Gallery, Art14, The Library Club. Beatrice played Nancy in Alison Murray's street Cult movie 'Mouth to Mouth'- Winner
    best film Brooklyn Film Festival, during 2015 she will play the lead role in Tony Ukpo's feature film 'The 17 Voices of Eloise Carmicheal'.
