    <p>
      <strong>Therese Steele</strong>
      is an artist working with performance and installation. She lived for several years in Beijing were she studied photography at The Beijing Film School.
      Therese has several academic degrees including Modern &amp; Classical Chinese and Politics from the infinite radical leftwing breeding ground of SOAS -
      School Of Oriental And African Studies - London as well as MA in Performance Design and Practice from Central Saint Martins. Her work has been shown at
      The Freud Museum, Artsadmin, Gallery8, Cochrane Theatre, Camden People’s theatre and Stockholm Fringe Festival.
    </p>
    <p>
      Therese collaborates with choreographer and artist Alice Tatge and their joint work deals with notions surrounding sexuality, body sovereignty and
      censorship. Their most recent large scale project, titled Dyad, developed during the riots in Istanbul 2013 is currently showing at Metamatic:Taf
      Athens.
